      "description": "Understand cryptographic techniques for secure model aggregation without revealing individual client updates.",
      "categories": ["privacy"],
      "difficulty": "advanced",
      "tags": ["privacy", "advanced"],
      "content": {
        "overview": "Secure aggregation allows a server to compute the sum of client updates without learning individual updates, enhancing privacy in federated learning.",
        "technical_details": "Protocols typically use techniques like secret sharing, homomorphic encryption, or secure multi-party computation.",
        "implementation": "Implementation considerations include communication overhead, computational complexity, and fault tolerance.",
        "challenges": "Key challenges include scaling to large numbers of participants and handling client dropouts during protocol execution."
      },
      "related_topics": ["diff-privacy", "privacy-fl"]
